        <div class="verdict">✓ Updated April 2026</div>

        <p>Commercial construction scheduling is a different beast than residential. You're coordinating dozens of subcontractors, managing critical path sequences, responding to owner-driven schedule changes, and often dealing with contract provisions that make delays expensive. The software has to match that complexity.</p>

        <p>Here's the honest breakdown of what works for commercial GCs, with no fluff about "ease of use" when what you actually need is power.</p>

